  "text": "consists of two time stamps corresponding to the start and end time of that read in the A-order (Z-order). We maintain each ordering by using a constant-time order-maintenance data structure [CITATION_1] [6]. Using these orderings, for all pairs of reads r 1 , r 2 we can check in constant time if re-execution of r1 must precede r2 or not: r1 precedes r2 in both orderings if this is the case, and if the orderings disagree then r1 and r2 are independent. Again, in Figure 4 we give the corresponding orderings. Although we define the orderings by a transversal of a completed computation tree it should be noted that in practice the orderings are created and updated as the tree is grown (i.e., the tree and total orderings are created and altered together using mutable data structures for an efficient implementation).",
